<part_of.title>Towers of Babel. Reproductions. Towers of Babel by other Artists.</part_of.title>

<parts.title>In Italy: in XV & XVI. Towers of Babel apparently only in Venice (to be explained by presence of Patenier's picture and Breviarium Grimani?) in several bookillustrations (see [Arthur M.] Hind, History of Woodcut, [London: Constable, 1935], (Venetian woodcuts may have influenced Holbein's woodcut of Babel)/ index; and [Leandro] Bassano (National Gallery, N° 60 - according to Mrs. Sauerländer); [verso] Breviarium Grimani was the source for Clovio's tower of Babel and perhaps for Bruegel last one too. Bruegel may have got to know Breviarium Grimani through Clovio. Query: since when was Scorel's Tower of Babel in Venice?</parts.title>
